 ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Personally, I frown on DOTs.  Unless fights get significanly longer at the higher levels, the amount of damage the DOT that actually lands before the MOB goes down in a good group is so small, it might as well be token.  How often does your DOT wear off before the end of a fight?  Is it really worth blowing the mana on a DOT in that situation?  Let's look at numbers here...<br>
<br>
Suffocate (Level 29)<br>
DD: 34-65 points<br>
STR Debuff: 15-20 points<br>
AGI Debuff: 15-20 points<br>
DOT: 198 hit points over 108 seconds.<br>
<br>
Gasping Embrace (Level 49)<br>
DD: 50 points<br>
STR Debuff: 29-30<br>
AGI Debuff: 29-30<br>
DOT: 660 hit points over 120 seconds.<br>
<br>
We can just write off the DD component.  A good melee can do more in the time it takes you to cast the DOT.  Let's look at the stat debuffs.  From what I recall from the previous posts on this subject, STR has little to no effect on the amount of damage a MOB can do.  The amount of STR these remove isn't going to have a huge effect on damage in any case.  The AGI debuff is about the same.  This removes a small amount of avoidance AC from the target.  And the DOT damage?  198 points over 108 seconds is 1.83 damage per second.  660 points over 120 seconds is 5.5 damage per second.  Next time you're in a group, ask your melee(s) how much damage they do per second.  I think you'll be surprised by the answer.  I know I was.  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Not to mention, once a MOB is DOTed, it can't be mezzed until the DOT wears off.  In some situations, this can become critical for you or your fellow party members if faced with a possible wipe-out.<br>
<br>
Now, I'm not saying that our DOTs don't have their uses.  Certainly, I have used my DOTs in many situations where I have been root-DOT soloing.  (You know, glazing over the part where I almost died because I suck at soloing.  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> )  Also, it can be incredibly useful when snare-kiting giants paired with a druid.  But, IMHO, the utility of our DOTs is limited at best.  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
If you are inclined to do some damage with your mana when in a group, I seriously suggest a...  What was the name someone used for it?  ...  'Hitpoint Debuff'  Good old-fashioned nuking, when timed well, can be of more benefit than a DOT in a good group.  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   Besides, it'll give you a chance to dust off that old Evocation skill!  (178 Evocation here.  Can ya tell I don't nuke much?  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> )  I can remember I turned up my lip at it when someone first suggested it, but it really can help a fight move along, and it tells the group the enchanter's bored when they see 'Saelia tells the group, &quot;Nuking &gt;&gt; a drachnid webmaster &lt;&lt; !!&quot;'  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Heh.  Sorry for the rant here.  This has been something I've wanted to get off my chest for a while.  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p><center><img src=http://home.netcom.com/~awachs/Sig9-47.JPG> <BR>
(We shall flow a river unto thee, and teeming with souls shall it ever be.)</center></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#D5D4D5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/ualundraadjani.showPublicProfile?language=EN>AlundraAdjani</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>I live here.... get out.</span><br> <font color=#000033>(8/1/01 11:23:22 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://alundraadjani.com/otherstuff/eq/catface.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Debuffing?</span><hr size=1> I like to nook. :P  I also don't use any debuffs besides tash and slow except really against ubermobs, but I do use dots against a lot of stuff in velious since a lot of it has a ton of hp and takes forever to keel (and some isn't mezzable anyhow).  Kael and SG come to mind especially.  Our dots are actually quite mana-efficient, even though they do take forever and don't do all that much damage. :P<br>
